org.jenetics

Class Population<G extends Gene<?,G>,C extends Comparable<? super C>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jenetics.Population<G,C>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Phenotype<G,C>>, Collection<Phenotype<G,C>>, List<Phenotype<G,C>>, RandomAccess, Copyable<Population<G,C>>

    public class Population<G extends Gene<?,G>,C extends Comparable<? super C>>
extends Object
implements List<Phenotype<G,C>>, Copyable<Population<G,C>>, RandomAccess, Serializable
    A population is a collection of Phenotypes.

    This class is not synchronized. If multiple threads access a Population concurrently, and at least one of the threads modifies it, it must be synchronized externally.
